          "created_at": "",
          "body": "I see value in this as I expect that the notion of \"known good initial starting position\" does matter for a rover as well. E.g. I could see that in real applications you don't want a rover to drive with its cruise speed from the parking position to the starting position (== too fast if it's moving near people).",
          "state": "APPROVED",
          "type": "review"
        }
      ]
    },
    "isLogicError": true,
    "logicErrorDescription": "Yes â€” the PR fixes incorrect mission-handling logic where takeoff waypoints were treated the same for all vehicle types, causing rovers to neither accept the waypoint (can't reach altitude) nor move (distance considered too close). The change adds a vehicle-type special case (use horizontal distance for rovers), correcting the conditional/acceptance logic so rovers can progress through missions that start with a takeoff waypoint."
